{"tid":2143993,"cid":1,"subCid":0,"title":"SpaceX 再次成功發射新一批Starlink及回收第一節火箭","createTime":"2020-08-07T11:52:57.000Z","updateTime":"2020-08-08T06:27:09.000Z","uid":295230,"like":4,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":4,"replies":[{"pid":"94f3cfc3da8cc87af2c1cf9e66f3269bfb7a107d","tid":2143993,"uid":295230,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-07T11:52:57.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KU6KogxG5BE\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DKU6KogxG5BE&d=ACvVw7CXGjn4pyDVYlJlLDcZFjLth35g1vO%2BxS%2F2N%2Fg%3D&h=c5cd0b0f\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KU6KogxG5BE</a><br />\n<br />\nSpaceX successfully launches its tenth set of Starlink internet satellites into orbit today.<br />\nAfter a prolonged delay, American aerospace manufacturer and space transportation services company, SpaceX, launched its ninth operational flight of internet satellites &lsquo;Starlink.&rsquo; The launch comes at the cost of three delays reaching back to late June due to weather and technical issues. The lift-off was at 1:12 a.m. ET (10:12 p.m. PT) on Friday, when the company&rsquo;s Falcon 9 rocket ascended from Pad 39A at NASA&rsquo;s Kennedy Space Center.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>SpaceX Launches Starlink &amp; BlackSky Satellites<br />\n</strong><br />\n<span class=\"red\">Falcon 9 successfully launched 57 Starlink internet satellites as well as two small Earth-imaging satellites into orbit under a rideshare agreement with Spaceflight</span>, Inc. It was Falcon 9&rsquo;s fifth spaceflight; meanwhile, Starlink made its eight liftoff this year, and the 10th overall (11 if you count the launch of two Starlink satellite prototypes in February 2018)."},{"pid":"a910da56320bd47ff186ae0565bfc091c2ff69fd","tid":2143993,"uid":295230,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-08-07T11:53:25.000Z","msg":"放左台....<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/a